Ok here goes the second version :). This one is
a more classical approach. All vampires are part
of one big family. They must receive the Dark Gift
from another PC vampire or from me. For each 
vampire the Dark Gift bestows them with different
abilities. The abilities that each Vampire receive
will be random. As they increase in age( I dont
think I will have guild levels, maybe they spend
thier experience to age or something. So a GL20
Vampire would be an Ancient or something. I
will come up with more romantic names as I get
further into it.) All vampire will receive one the 
same. The ability to draw blood from the victem.
This blood siphoned will add to the Vampires
store of blood. (I wont call it a blood pool if you
dont want but I feel its a generic enough term :)
As a vampire wanders through life thier blood
will slowly be used up. As it gets lower and lower
the vampire will get penalties to thier actions and
start to get massive cravings. They will have a 
base blood pool level based on thier age. If they
go below this base they will get the penalties. The
vampire may also go above this base and receive
increased strength and a sense of euphoric drunk-
eness. This will be how vampire get drunk as
alcohol will not affect them. The can also get drunk
by drinking off a PC who is drunk or stoned. Food
will also not affect a vampire as they are dead and 
have absolutely no need to eat. Blood is thier
food and drink. To be fair though, things like 
drowning and poison should not affect them. This
will have to be up to the wizard who makes such
items to decide though. I would like it if they
could traverse the sea without penalty:). Another
penalty of Vampires is that travelling in ANY
outdoors areas that are lit will damage them.
Maybe a call_out() of every 10 secs or so to
query thier environment and will do some damage
to them. This damage will have to be more than
one per heartbeat so maybe 4 per 10 secs? The 
numbers will have to come through testing cause
its kinda mean having them perishing to quickly
out there. Effectively they WILL NOT be able
to heal in a lit area. Also xp reqs for both normal
levels and guild levels will be more stringent. They
will get bonus's on stat advancement for str/con/
int/dex.  In the dark they will receive faster regen
rates. Escepcially if they are high on blood. Benefits
at the guild hall (I will be putting this in my own
Necropolis type city and it will be called the 
Theatre De' Vampires. I dont think AR will mind
as I have already ripped off my chars name from
her anyway :) will include coffins for each 
vampire that they can store stuff in and rest in for
added healing power. BTW this city will be
permanently dark so they can travel without 
harm but it will be a ways from ML darkwind. Oh
yeah, vampires will get a better ac as they go up
level as they become increasingly harder to damage
and thier skin becomes harder. When they start
getting REALLY old the damage they sustain in
the sun decreases to.


OK heres the powers list:
Heightened Senses type thing: Vamps can see players
that are hiding, can track things etc.

Locate Person: They can free thier mind and send it
across the MUD to locate where a person is.

Read minds: They can follow the person around kinda
like a snoop? Dunno is this will be allowed

Flight: The vampire can fly around. I am not to sure
of the game benefits of this power yet.

Shapechange into various animals: Just like it says.
The different forms will be rat, cat, bat and wolf.

Form of mist: Let the Vampire turn into a mist form
and float away.

Dissapear: Hiding ability. Starts of weak bit at high
levels will be able to go unseen in darkplaces.

Control Emotion: Will make a monster/player
aggressive or non-aggressive.

Mesmerise: While the vampire stares into the targets
eyes they cannot move or do anything.

Awe: Targets become extremely impressed with the
vampires power. Bonus to char.

Night sight: Like it says.

Taloned hands: The nails on the Vampires hand can
grow out into long talons which are very sharp.

Meld into the earth: Allows the vampire to escape into
the loving embrace of the earth.

Manipulate Shadows: Make little shadow puppet 
thingamies. 

Death Mark: The target is marked for death by all
vampires.

Speed: Allows the vampire to move in a blur of
motion for brief periods of time.

Burning things: Will begin with inanimate objects
made of paper and wood but will eventually go
onto less combustable materials then onto living
flesh.

Telekinesis: Can move objects around without 
touching them. Advanced form would be to squeeze
a persons heart till it stopped :)

Dread Gaze: The target instantly flees away from
the Vampire.

And any more that Vader or I can think of
laters :)

Also the only guilds I really know the powers for
are Necros and Psions. If these powers are
to much like other guilds let me know so I can
maybe change em.

Like I said they will get a random couple of 
powers to begin with and each time the reach a
new milestone on thier aging they will receive 
a new random power. Each power starts off weak
but gets more powerful as the Vampire get older.
Eventually a TRUELY ANCIENT vampire will get
all the powers but hopefully this will take a while.
By TRUELY ANCIENT I am meaning like 50th+
level. I want this guild to be one that will be good 
for players 20+. That is all for this doc for now. 
it was good reading.

BTW this is just a basic outline. I have lotsa emotes
for them and plenty of atmospheric stuff. I dont
have the time to write everything down :)

Also I dont know if I mentioned before but 
only humans and maybe elves can be vampires. I
dont have any real logical bases except my
preference :)

Oh btw.....Weapons and Armor restrictions. No HUGE weapons and no platemail type armor.
